&lt;p>Create several tables to handle the different components of the JSON data. The main tables could be:&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>&lt;strong>&lt;code>domains&lt;/code>&lt;/strong>: Store basic information about the domain.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>&lt;strong>&lt;code>appraisal&lt;/code>&lt;/strong>: Store appraisal values and related data.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>&lt;strong>&lt;code>keyword_stats&lt;/code>&lt;/strong>: Store keyword statistics.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>&lt;strong>&lt;code>sales_history&lt;/code>&lt;/strong>: Store historical sales data.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>&lt;strong>&lt;code>trademarks&lt;/code>&lt;/strong>: Store trademark information.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>&lt;strong>&lt;code>web&lt;/code>&lt;/strong>: Store web-related statistics.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>&lt;strong>&lt;code>whois&lt;/code>&lt;/strong>: Store WHOIS-related data.&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
